result.execSummary:
The defendant Bronson J. Bantleon was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Proceedings 02-05-16
Reporter Jill Bartol

Defendant Bronson J. Bantleon in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Defendant Bronson J. Bantleon in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee states plea agreement to Ct. 1.  Ct 2 to be dismissed and read-in.  Atty Hendee states that the State and the Defense is waiving a PSI being done.  Atty Gumz agrees and states that the defendant has already given a DNA Sample and asks that the surcharge be waived.  Court questions the defendant.  Defendant agrees and enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed.

Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations and asks the court to follow the joint recommendation.   State has complied with victim notification requirements.
Atty Gumz states that the defendant waives a PSI.
Atty Gumz makes sentencing arguments and states that the defendant is serving a Prison sentence at this time.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.

BY THE COURT:  Ct. 1:  Court orders 4 1/2 years in the Wisconsin State Prison System with 1 year Initial Confinement and 3 1/2 years Extended Supervision with conditions; consecutive to any other sentence
